      <heading>Mon Nov 22 (Larannea)   :: 1: ranks (complete)</heading>
      <slot>1</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>.  Guarded - those that have runaway from the Tower, and are being
.             held to be returned. Also people that are taken prisoner
.             by the Kin for whatever reason.
.
.  Patient - People who cannot just be healed, maybe mental patients,
.            and that have been brought to a location where the guild
.            operates where they will be nurtured back to health.
.
.  Apprentice - Once a woman is taken in by the Kin, she begins a
.            training that attempts to emulate the training they had
.            previously received.
.            There are 5 subranks for Apprentices:
.               Apprentice Initiate
.               Apprentice Practiced
.               Apprentice Advanced
.               Apprentice Prepared
.               Apprentice Learned
.            Advancement through these 5 ranks depends on a loose
.            syllabus and active RP with Wise Women and Elders.
.  
.  Trusted - The people who perform 'support' functions within the Kin.
.            This can range anywhere from defense, to spying to being
.            married to a Kinswoman. This role is open to both men and
.            women.
.            Subranks are:
.               Trusted student 
.               Trusted defender
.               Trusted lookout
.               Trusted husband 
.               Trusted crafter
.
.  Wise Woman - Once done with your Apprentice Training, you
.            become a full Wise Woman, and can begin a Healing shop if you
.            so choose. Since the Kin focus a lot on healing weaves, and
.            since many of the Kin were Wise Woman trained in the Ebou Dari
.            tradition, there is an abundance of healers in the Kin. Most
.            Kin know beyond the basics of healing using the One Power.
.            There are 7 subranks for Wise Women to choose from:
.            Scholar    - those who study and wish to learn
bookworms.
.            Philosopher- those who take themselves up with the questions of life.
.            Seeker     - those who spend their time finding runaways and other
.                           girls from the Tower.
.            Healer     - those who heal beyond the normal
.            Protector   - those who choose to protect the Kin and guards its
.                           secrecy.
.            Mediator   - those who wish to spend their time mediating the many
.                           quarrels of their native city of Ebou Dar, as well as
.                           others.
.            Traveler   - those who spend their time in other lands, healing and
.                           gathering information, spending their time on various
.                           causes.
.
.  Mistress of the Runaways - She takes care of those who have run away fr
.            the Tower.
.  Mistress of Herbs - She is responsible for finding and researching herbs
.            as well for the parts of the syllabus that deals with
.            herbs in all its aspects.
.  Mistress of Apprentices - She arranges the lessons and advancement of
.            Apprentices.
.  Mistress of Discipline - For those Apprentices that misbehave.
.  Mistress of Trusted - The one responsible for the people in the trusted rank.
.  Elder   - A rank given to older kinsmembers, showing they have helped and
.            guided the Kin to their best effort. Because of the wisdom that
.            comes with age their advice is highly respected.
.  Eldest - the GL rank :)
</text>
    </message>
