      <heading>Tue Apr 18 (Caitlyn)    :: &amp;CChanneling Syllabus&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>3</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Initiate (Level I);
 
Lecture: Kin Laws and Structure
Lecture:  Behaviour
Lesson: Basic Herb Use
Lesson: Finding Herbs
To Advance: quest to find herbs;
 
Channeler (Level II)
 
Test of Channeling Abilities
Whichever of the Following are Necessary:
Lesson: Grasp/Release
Lecture: Observing the Aura of the One Power
Lesson: Working With the Five Flows
 
Plus the following:
Lesson: Minor Healing with the One Power
Lesson: Intermediate herb use
Observe and assist in one healing session
 
In either level I or II:
Lecture or Report: Kin History
Lecture or Report: Ebou Dari Culture (with possible IC tour)
 
Intermediate (Level 3)
 
(in no particular order)
Lecture: Role of a Wise Woman
Lesson: Advanced healing with the One Power
Lesson: Shielding
Lesson(s): other useful weaves
Assist with 2 (or more) healing sessions
 
Diagnose and treat one (or more) patient(s), with supervision.
Speak with a member in your Specialization (subrank)
</text>
