      <heading>Wed Aug 23 (Larannea)   :: &amp;cThe red belt\c00</heading>
      <slot>7</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Hiya,

It has been brought to my attention that some of the AS might know
about the connection of the Kin to the red belt ICly. Personally, I
doubt such a statement, eventho the person that brought it forwards
is, in my eyes, reasonably trustworthy when it comes to this kind of
things.

The red belt, added to that, is the only truly IC piece of equipment
the Kin has...With IC I mean that it can be traced back to the books.
As such, it is a very important piece of equipment. It should also
be noted that the belt wasnt worn -all- the time, but that wise women
were chosen to wear the belt and act out on the responsibilities it
brought with it for a certain amount of time. A job that wasnt very
liked by wise women on average, if I remember correctly. The tasks
of those that are wearing the belt is to provide healing to whomever
needs it, added to that, there were probably also other tasks that
came with it. Examples of these tasks could be, for instance, mediating
between two fighting parties and such. At any rate, in Ebou Dar the
red belt was known, respected and maybe even feared. Outside of Ebou
Dar (and the Rahad) it was hardly known by anyone.

Those of you that do not feel comfortable with wearing the red belt all
of the time icly under these circumstances while you do feel your
equipment has IC bearing might consider doing the same trick as many
of the AS do: writing a small statement underneath their desc telling
players under what circumstances the red belt should be considered to
be IC.

Laran.
</text>
