      <heading>Mon Sep 25 (Daene)      :: Daene visits Bradden's bed... </heading>
      <slot>12</slot>
      <level>121</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>During the day, the orphanage's corridors usually stood quiet 
and empty.  This particular afternoon passed in languorous 
idleness, silence indoors broken only by the distant, muted 
sounds of children playing in the sunshine.  
Then, into this den of tranquillity, scampered two figures.  
Sticking to the shadows, the clandestine figures -skulked-, 
emitting hushed scheming whispers.  The taller figure, 
obviously the leader, held a tiny pot in one hand, and her 
friends hand in the other.
All was well until the smaller figure, quite obviously one 
of the orphanage's children, tripped, letting out a soft 
yelp and a whispered, 'Are you sure this is a good idea, Daene?' 
The older woman nodded, but couldn't stall a tittering laugh.  
Catastrophe followed mishap; as Daene lifted one hand to stifle 
her giggles, there was a poof dust from the container - Pepper!  
Daene sneezed violently, and her co-conspirator giggled, 
wrinkling her (unbelievably) cute nose as the powder sifted 
down through the air.  Decorum vanished as the two struggled 
through a fit of giggling.. yet when Daene finally sobered, 
they continued on through the corridor, towards a particular 
guardsman's room.  Daene led, unerring - as though perhaps she'd 
been here before, or had followed someone here - and they stole 
quietly into Bradden's bedroom.
Pouncing into action, Daene flung back the sheets and liberally 
dosed the bed in the offending pepper, carefully making sure that 
there wasn't enough to leave smudges, but certainly enough to make 
sleep impossible.  Daene winked at her shorter (and very very 
adorable) companion, and deftly remade the bed.
Then, as if that wasn't mischief enough, nimble fingers slipped a 
note from some hidden pocket and tucked it, out of sight, under the 
mans pillow - and wearing a decidedly pleased smirk, Daene let her 
young friend drag her from the room.   


*OOC*  You'll notice I didn't exactly say who the girl was.
I'm sure somebody will work it out... 
</text>
