      <text>Righty, I can't make the meeting (GMT sucks, I know), but I'd been 
working with Laran on some things.  With the change of admin.. well, 
I'll open the ideas here and you guys can argue over them.
&amp;WActivity/Members&amp;n
We -cannot- get more members until we have an active rp area.
At the last meeting, we talked about either refinding the orphanage,
and getting it put back in, or rebuilding it.  Likewise, the Kin farm
that was to be based just outside of Caemlyn.  I've built most of 
the farm already, mapped it and desc'd it, so all that needs done 
is to get it in place.  

A while ago Cait mentioned getting some Kinnies into Houses, as
teachers, healers, etc.  I know they aren't the most active guild
on the mud, but could we bug them about it?
Oh, oh the orphanage side again.. once its in place, how about
we mention it on the OOC board, and post that all children char's
are welcome to both play there, and be guilded to the Kin as
'Orphan' or even just 'Child'.  Obviously we'd have to make joining
worth something.. like some kind of skill, and of course g.eq.  
Look at it this way, they could also use the fact that if they get
trouble they could do a runner to the orphanage - and NPC (within
reason) one of the Kinnies taking care of them.

&amp;WSyllabus&amp;n  (for channelers, anway)
How about taking after one of the *cough* other guilds on this one.
Get the actual -content- of the lectures writen down, on the web
somewhere we can all get to.  An IC section, on what should be known,
hints on rp'ing it and stuff, and an OOC section for any other details.
I've got examples of this waiting to go, if anybody wants to see what 
I mean.
Obviously, you -cannot- teach somebody how to rp channeling by just
letting them read a file, then giving them rank.  If channeling lessons
are taught this way, the student would have to be tested - either somebody
of higher rank actually testing them, or using other chars/npc'ing 
situations to test them.  Want an example?  Due to a lack of teachers,
I learn all I need to know about weave healing from the file.  Then
the GL, or anybody of a decent enough higher rank, rp's out a situation
whereby they -need- healing, either as themselves or using an alt, or 
whatever.  If I rp it out well enough, doing everything right, its assumed
that I know what I'm doing, and pass the lecture/lesson.
So many things could be done this way - and if its done wrong?  THEN
I'd get taught how to do it, shown ic'ly or ooc'ly what I did wrong
and how to impove it.  Its just plain silly having people that know
perfectly well what they are doing resit all these lessons and lectures
when we lack the members to teach them.  We HAVE experience, so why not 
use it to our advantage??
I'm sure you can see how almost all channeler lectures could be done
this way, if the file's were writen up correctly.
Full examples on demand.

-D.
</text>
