      <heading>Tue Nov 28 (Bradden)    :: An accident</heading>
      <slot>15</slot>
      <level>43</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>Joram pulled himself up onto the next tree branch and smiled triumphantly.  He
had done it.  He had climbed higher than any of the other children at the
Orphanage.  Settling himself on the branch, he looked up at the sun and closed
his eyes, letting the warm light wash over him.  Suddenly, a loud cracking
noise caused his youthful eyes to open, and the last thing he saw as the branch
broke out from underneath him, was the ground rushing up at him.  He shrieked
for a moment before hitting the ground.  Blackness engulfed him.  His ear
suddenly perked up as he rounded the corner of the building nearest the garden.
Eyes wide, he bolted toward the shriek.  Upon reaching the scene, he gasped in
shock.  Laying there upon the ground, was Joram, his left arm bent at an odd
angle behind his back.  Unmoving, Bradden thought the boy dead, and this
opinion wasd enforced more by the shock he was in, which would not allow him to
hear the soft breathing of the unconcious youth.  Throwing his head back, he
howled in fury and sadness.  Thoughts were running through his head, unsortable
in their extremity.  Why hadn't he gotten there sooner?  Why had he not been
watching the children better?  Why?  Why?  Why?  As several other guards and a
couple of the women working at the Orphanage showed up, Bradden turned his gaze
upon them, lost in his grief and rage.  With a snarl, he turned and bolted.  
Reaching the wall with the guards in pursuit, he leapt, catching the edge.  
Climbing over, he dropped to the ground and ran, heading for the south.    
</text>
