      <heading>Thu Dec  7 (Daene)      :: &amp;WForgetting the Past&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>16</slot>
      <level>121</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>She didn't sleep well, that night.  

She never did, really, but that night it seemed somehow worse,
somehow more lonely, knowing He wasn't there.  Reliving 
everything she'd said, everything she'd done to him.. 
everything she'd denied him.  It was almost physical, that 
ache, and eventually she rose, started pacing the room - 
His room, although he hadn't been there for hours.  
At first light, she left the orphanage.. set out on the 
streets, just wandering, searching, maybe getting lost, 
then refinding herself.  For hours she simply wandered - 
until she found, at the end of a rather dirty little lane,
a man.  
One of the old men watching from nearby overheard
only a little of the conversation - she seemed to know 
this man, or think she did, and accuse him of something,
going so far as to even draw her belt knife on him!
  
What happened next was confused.. the rumours ran in so 
many directions that nobody really seemed to know had gone 
on - simply that the ground around the man exploded, the 
earth erupting and stones and rocks flying.  
The woman was seen leaving, dark hair matted against her 
skull with blood, and a rather confused expression on 
her face.   


***  Log on demand.  And no, Daene isn't dead.  She simply has no idea who she is, who anybody else is, or even where she is.  And she's a much happier person for it  *grin*  if anybody's looking, she can be found at Inn's around the city, performing her art ***
</text>
