      <text>We are in the middle of change. Krisa and I are going to need to speak
with all of you when you log in next so please send us tells. I'll give
you a brief rundown of what we are doing, but most is going to depend on
you and what you choose to do with your characters.

Right now, the novice book in the Rebel Tower is open, due to a decision
made by the Amyrlin, Egwene al'Vere. She wants all channelers to be
associated with the Tower directly. This doesn't mean that -anyone- can
become Aes Sedai, but if you channel, she wants to know and wants you
around. What this is coming down to OOC, is a merger between Kin and the
Rebels. We are going to be shifting the Kin guild into the Rebels, more
or less. ICly, they know you are here and know what you are about. A note
has been sent to Krisa from the Hall of Sitters asking her to come and
speak with them. If everything goes well, we should be able to guild you
to the Rebels with some changes to EQ and such depending on what you do
with your characters, give you a rank, all that jazz. Once the changes
are in place, then you'll be ranked in the Rebels and the ranking with
the stand along Kin guild will dissolve. You'll be the same, with a
guild, but not this one specifically.

There is low membership, in case you hadn't noticed, and a lot of things
have happened or certain things put in place that aren't exactly what the
Kin were in the books. We're going to try and change that, restructure,
look over, and evaluate how things should be handled. We aren't deguilding
you and leaving you without, just merging.

If you can, please talk with either myself or with Krisa about what you
want to do and the latest developments. Get ready for the strings to your
ankles and wrists that Aes Sedai can provide.  *grin*

Have some fun with it. Maybe it will help numbers and RP situations.
